<explanation interaction="true">
<para> The student uses the Everglades as an example in response to the professor's
question regarding uncontrolled development (D). He is not introducing a new
topic (A) even though he does bring up birds&ndash;as an example. And he is
not arguing with the professor (B)in fact he is providing support for the
idea that development hurts wildlife. The student's response is not connected
to seals (C) in any way.</para>
